title: Google\Cloud\ServiceUsage\V1\DisableServiceRequest
name: DisableServiceRequest
description:
Request message for the DisableService method.

Generated from protobuf message google.api.serviceusage.v1.DisableServiceRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the consumer and service to disable the service on. The enable and disable methods currently only support projects. An example name would be: projects/123/services/serviceusage.googleapis.com where 123 is the project number.

params.name: data.disable_dependent_services
params.description: Indicates if services that are enabled and which depend on this service should also be disabled. If not set, an error will be generated if any enabled services depend on the service to be disabled. When set, the service, and any enabled services that depend on it, will be disabled together.

params.name: data.check_if_service_has_usage
params.description: Defines the behavior for checking service usage when disabling a service.
